## Linux User & Permission Security

### What is a User in Linux?
A user is an identity that can log in and perform actions on a Linux system.

### Types of Users
- Root User: Has full system access
- Normal User: Limited permissions
- System User: Used by services

### What are Permissions?
Permissions define who can:
- Read (r)
- Write (w)
- Execute (x)

### Permission Levels
- Owner
- Group
- Others

### Why Permissions Matter in Cybersecurity?
- Prevents unauthorized access
- Protects sensitive files
- Limits damage during attacks

### Command Used
chmod – used to change file permissions